  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex> be the residue field of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> the residue field of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>.
      Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is flat over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L=B\otimes _A k]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}=\mathfrak {m}B]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {m}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}]]></fr:tex> are the maximal ideals of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> respectively), the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {m}]]></fr:tex>-adic filtration on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is identical to the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}]]></fr:tex>-adic filtration, and
      <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {gr}^\bullet (B) = \operatorname {gr}^\bullet (A)\otimes _k L.       ]]></fr:tex>
      It follows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {gr}^\bullet (B)]]></fr:tex> is a polynomial algebra over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {gr}^\bullet (A)]]></fr:tex> is a polynomial algebra over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex>.
      (N.B. we have not used the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L/k]]></fr:tex> is separable.)</fr:p>
